org.dice_research.squirrel.data.uri.group

Interface UriGroupByOperator<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the class of the key

    public interface UriGroupByOperator<T>
    A URI group by operator defines they way how several URIs are transformed into groups or chunks of URIs based on a certain key value they share.
    Author:
    Michael Röder (michael.roeder@uni-paderborn.de)

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods Default Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      default Map<T,List<CrawleableUri>> groupByKey(Collection<CrawleableUri> uris)
      Transforms the given set of URIs into groups based on their key values that are retrieved for each of them.
      T retrieveKey(CrawleableUri uri)
      Retrieves the key value (i.e., the identifier of its group) from the given URI

    • Method Detail

      • retrieveKey

        Retrieves the key value (i.e., the identifier of its group) from the given URI

      • groupByKey
